## Ethics
* Why do people cheat?


### Risk
* risk = expected outcome * likelihood


### Cheating makes you a cheater
* Moral corruption & physiological habits
* Inevitable conclusion
* Addictive behavior
* Enlightened self-interest


### Modern Reality
* Constant surveillance
* Data logs every action
* Powerful people have access to your data


### Technology makes it easy
* Dangerous temptation is always there
* You must remember the consequence and likelihood of discovery


### The Mom Rule
* Mindset - Everything you do will be published in a newspaper article that your mom will read.
* Everything will come to light eventually


### Personal Story
* Several lives in ruins


### MCB take Ethics Seriously
* Consequences for Students Cheating
    * zero on assignment
    * flunk the class
    * eliminated from MCB
    

